01/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The National Service for Fight against Organised Crime says nearly 5m euros in EU funds extended under the SAPARD programme have been misappropriated. Interior Minister Rumen Petkov said on Sunday (30 April) that the cases in question were in Dobrich, Plovdiv and Sliven. Petkov refused to disclose specifics but said officials from regional agriculture agencies were involved. (Monitor - 01/05/06; bTV, Darik - 30/04/06)
